class DigitRecognitionModel(tf.keras.Model):
    def _init_(self):
        super()._init_()
        self.flatten = tf.keras.layers.Flatten()
        self.dense1 = tf.keras.layers.Dense(128, activation='relu')
        self.dropout = tf.keras.layers.Dropout(0.2)
        self.output_layer = tf.keras.layers.Dense(10, activation='softmax')

    def call(self, inputs, training=False):
        x = self.flatten(inputs)
        x = self.dense1(x)
        x = self.dropout(x, training=training)
        return self.output_layer(x)

Answer
This code defines a custom neural network model for digit recognition using TensorFlow Keras model subclassing.
DigitRecognitionModel extends tf.keras.Model
_init_() defines the layers:
Flatten converts 28×28 images into a 1D vector
Dense(128, relu) learns features
Dropout(0.2) reduces overfitting during training
Dense(10, softmax) outputs probabilities for digits 0–9
call() defines the forward pass
training=False ensures dropout is applied only during training
